Reasoning: Considering the patient's description of being below the poverty line and living in an unsafe neighborhood, it is likely that he may have limited access to healthy food options, healthcare resources, and safe environments for exercise. These factors can contribute to the progression of heart failure and the need for monitoring fluid intake to prevent complications.

